{"lemma":"يَسْرَةُ","slug":"يَسْرَةُ","root":"#.س.ر","root_slug":"_-س-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-س-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42453","n42462"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42453","headword_ar":"يسّرهُ","root":"ysr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tayosiyrN","text_ar":"تَيْسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, &c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God, A, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered it, easy; facilitated it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, Mgh, Msb, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yus~irato EalayohaA","text_ar":"يُسِّرَتْ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwilaAdapu","text_ar":"الوِلَادَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The act of bringing forth was rendered easy to her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his circumstances ample; he made his condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his way"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lika*aA","text_ar":"لِكَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he accommodated, adapted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposed, him,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloyusoraY","text_ar":"لِلْيُسْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to easy things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the easier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easiest, way"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S. A, [in the latter of which this is given as a proper, not tropical, signification:]) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he prepared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made ready, him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lika*aA","text_ar":"لِكَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A [in which this signification is said to be tropical.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tayosiyrN","text_ar":"تَيْسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"relates to both good and evil: (M, K:) as in the following instances in the Kur; [xcii. 7, 10;]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fasanuyas~iruhu liloyusoraY","text_ar":"فَسَنُيَسِّرُهُ لِلْيُسْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloEusoraY","text_ar":"لِلْعُسْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will facilitate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth, his way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will accommodate him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adapt him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispose him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a state of ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a state of difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (as explained in the TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Esr","text_ar":"عسر"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to punishment, and a difficult case:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will prepare him for paradise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for hell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will prepare him to return to good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous, conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to persevere in evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unrighteous, conduct;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the former leading to ease, and the latter to difficulty:] (Fr, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will prepare him for that habit of conduct which leads to ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as the entering paradise, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for that which leads to difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as the entering hell: from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ys~r Alfarasa","text_ar":"يسّر الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he prepared the horse for riding, by saddling and bridling."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) It is said in a trad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqado yus~ira lahu","text_ar":"وَقَدْ يُسِّرَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TahuwrN","text_ar":"طَهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And water for ablution had been prepared and put for him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yas~ara Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"يَسَّرَ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tayosiyrN","text_ar":"تَيْسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man's camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, brought forth with ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M, K),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and none of them perished."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yas~arati Alganamu","text_ar":"يَسَّرَتِ الغَنَمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, abounded in milk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K,) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the S, M, A, but in the K or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they brought forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they were ready to bring forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they abounded."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) A poet (namely Aboo-Useydeh Ed-Debeeree, TA) says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"humaA say~idaAnaA yazoEumaAni wA_in~amaA\n                      \n                     \n                        yasuwdaAninaA A^ano yas~arato ganamaA humaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are our two chiefs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they assert; but they are only our chiefs inasmuch as their sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, abound in milk and in offspring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayosarato","text_ar":"اَيْسَرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["God","A","Msb","Sb","M","K","S","Jel","Fr","TA","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n42462","headword_ar":"يَسْرَةٌ","root":"ysr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasaArN","text_ar":"يَسَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}